Age, Biography and Wiki

Austin O'Brien is an American actor and photographer. He is best known for his roles in the films Last Action Hero (1993), The Lawnmower Man 2: Beyond Cyberspace (1996), and Little Giants (1994). O'Brien was born on May 11, 1981 in Eugene, Oregon. He began his acting career at the age of seven, appearing in commercials and television shows. He made his feature film debut in the 1993 action-comedy Last Action Hero, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger. O'Brien went on to appear in a number of films, including Little Giants (1994), The Lawnmower Man 2: Beyond Cyberspace (1996), and The Stupids (1996). He also had a recurring role on the television series 7th Heaven. In recent years, O'Brien has focused on his photography career. He has shot for a number of magazines, including GQ, Esquire, and Vogue. As of 2021, Austin O'Brien's net worth is estimated to be roughly $2 million.

Timeline

Austin Taylor O'Brien (born May 11, 1981) is an American actor and photographer. He may be best known for playing the co-lead Danny Madigan in the Arnold Schwarzenegger-movie Last Action Hero, followed by his turn into romance as Nick Zsigmond in My Girl 2, a part in both The Lawnmower Man and its sequel, and as Josh Greene in the CBS drama Promised Land. He originally gained fame from a Circuit City commercial as a kid who, after finding out he'd saved money, says, "Cool" to the store's employee.
